title: I needed someone to export latex products and import potato chips and Kel Varnsen didn't let me down!
reviews: Great company! Couldn't say enough good things about the gentleman in charge of the place. His name was George Costanza. He said he was an importer and an exporter. I was blown away by that statement. I had always thought you had to be one or the other. An importer or an exporter but not both. He said he did both. At a place called Vandelay Industries. Yeah that's right. I believe he imported latex products and exported I think potato chips...might be wrong about the chips. I'm not sure what it was but he did both jobs. He worked with a fellow by the name of Kel Varnsen. Great bunch of people they have working over there at Vandelay

title: Their services are highly appreciated
reviews: Their services are highly appreciated. Are there hiccups sometimes, yes, but honestly if you've been in the import and export business for any reasonable period of time, you'll know that these guys are at the top of their game and offer truly something really different.

title: Been a private label seller
reviews: Been a private label seller since 2015. Found coshipper a year ago and they have taken great care of all of our supply chain and shipping needs, so we can now focus better on growing business. All our inventories have been moved with great care and zero damage until now. Hoping the same services for future as well. And, their charges are competitive as compared to other similar companies. Time wise, it’s as expected: A few days off estimated transit times and delays at customs, but come on people, did you not realize there’s an pandemic! This is why you plan your inventory and arrange your supplies restock schedules ahead of time with sufficient buffer. “Just in time inventory” planning is not gonna work when there’s a global disease that’s killed close to 500k people here in the US, and impacted millions. If you think your suppliers or service providers are responsible for keeping your products in stock in light of what’s happening, I’m sorry Buddy, but no - it’s your problem. Delays are gonna happen, so my advice to fellow sellers is to change how your planning your inventory and your restock times to account for a changing world. rant over

title: Thumbs up.

I got my shipment confirmation from Jaelyn after payment and it was honestly a big relief. Keep helping like this!!

title: Coshipper has really helped

title: Coshipper delivered our LCL
reviews: Coshipper delivered our LCL ocean on time. Their services are highly appreciated. Also, there was no damage done to the products.

title: BUYER BEWARE. Take a look at their "positive" reviews and the reviewers that left them
reviews:
TWO extremely poor experiences with Coshipper for my shipment from China to USA. Their quotes for their transit times are as true as unicorns and fairies. They may be listed on Amazon's vendors list for shipping but trust that it won't be long - they are absolutely the worst shipping service you could pick. Do not say you weren't warned - they will give you the runaround for any status you ask for after you pay (they do not provide third party tracking, just their own manual tracking which they update with any info as they please). Plagued with dishonesty and confusion, they do not take ANY responsibility for their poor services.

Here are some excuses (I received all 4) you may hear when the goods have not been delivered. Mind you they picked up the goods in SEPTEMBER 2020 and this is in JANUARY 2021:
1. We are unable to make a delivery appointment. We have been urging every day
2. The goods have already been delivered. When asked the date, they then realize it hasn't been delivered
3. The goods need to be dismantled from the shelf
4. The goods were stuck in customs for weeks causing delay

As another reviewer said, DO NOT FALL FOR IT! We have since disputed the payment on PayPal as they have lost all credibility. They are now trying to ask me to wire them more money directly to their bank account. What a nightmare. It will be an expensive and frustrating lesson for you. Don't learn the hard way.

title: The staff is amazing
reviews: The staff is amazing! Very helpful and considerate with a sense of urgency. Loads are 99% on time and the rates are very competitive. I look forward to doing business with them for many years to come.

title: 5 stars!!!
reviews: Your team worked magnificently all through the year and especially at year-end......Glad that I trusted y'all for handling my shipments. 5 stars!!!

title: The best international shipping service, I must say.
reviews: Sending goods from GZ for a long time. Every shipment has reached to the destinations as scheduled with just a few delays. Thank you Henry for sending the shipment details as well and keeping me updated. Wish covid can be over!!

title: Coshipper always does the sourcing
reviews:
Coshipper always does the sourcing (yes, they helped me find some products and contracted out to the factories directly) and the logistics part of shipment of our products to Amazon warehouses straight out from China + splitting shipment to a few of my client's large warehouses (for further distribution) in the US. Their services are highly appreciated. Are there hiccups sometimes, yes, but honestly if you've been in the import and export business for any reasonable period of time (8 years for myself), you'll know that these guys are at the top of their game and offer truly something really different.

Also a tip, I've asked them to QC for any damages to my products before they ship out, and there have been no damages due to transit to the products either so far. My advise to some is to make sure you get the best packaging possible at the manufacture side, and to make sure QC is done before you ship out or else its very hard to find the ones accountable as your distributors or end customers are gonna complain to you if and when truth hits the fan. Coshipper side, 5/5.

title: Delayed delivery - damaged goods - Horrible experience and big loss
reviews: I had a really bad experience with Coshipper for my shipment from China to France. The shipment arrived damaged (on top of being delayed by over a month) and Coshipper did not want to take responsibility for it inspite of having shipping insurance. What's worse is that they stopped responding to my questions/requets through multiple communication channels. We had a big financial loss and it's sad to see that such unprofessional companies are still fooling people. DON'T FALL FOR THE TRAP.

title: Excellent shipping service

title: DO NOT TRUST

Save yourself the despair and DO NOT work with this company. Lawsuit on its way.

title: We are an importer and exporter for the…
reviews: We are an importer and exporter for the last 8 years. We took a chance on using a 3rd party to work with. This is one of those business decisions you scratch your head and ask yourself why you didn’t make this decision years ago. We are proud to call ourselves a client of Coshipper. Part of our problem was we had so many different business needs to attend to and not enough time to complete daily tasks. Working with Coshipper enabled us to spend our time on the other operational and marketing tasks, and less on sourcing and supply chain. I have 100% faith in this team. I’m quite sure I’ll be learning from them as the shipments keep coming in. This is a first class operation. If you have any doubts then I suggest you make an appointment for a visit at their office in Shanghai and meet these folks. I can now spend more time focusing on product development and marketing needs while they handle our China side consolidation and supply chain.

title: Bad experience...Disappointed.
reviews:
We tried Coshipper because of these 5-star reviews. We selected the fastest shipping option which was supposed to take around 11 – 18 days and even settled the full cost initially. This was all to make sure that we got the best service that they could offer. Shipping was initiated in late June. Now we’re in the month of August and our goods still haven’t been delivered. This was a very sad experience for us considering this was our first try with Coshipper. We would like this issue to be resolved as soon as possible.

Update: The rest of the goods were delivered on the 19th of August.
